        <profileDesc>
            <creation/>
            <abstract>
                <p>A long historiographic work in Amharic, attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BDLaethf28">Oxford, Bodleian Library, Bodleian Aeth. f. 28</ref> (where it occupies c. 120 pages), containing various genealogies
                    and chronologies of Biblical figures, Ethiopian kings and Church history, accounts of the rule of Ethiopian kings and further sections dealing with the
                    hierarchies of Ethiopian notables and other topics.
                    A relation to <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2422Tarika">Tārika nagaśt</ref> is possible.</p>
            </abstract>
